{# Problem Strip section #}
<section class="py-5 py-lg-6 bg-cream-deep" id="problem">
  <div class="container-xl">
    <div class="mb-5">
      <span class="priam-eyebrow">The reality for SMBs</span>
      <h2 class="priam-section-title mt-2">Risk doesn't wait for you to be ready.</h2>
      <p class="lead mt-3" style="max-width: 64ch; color: var(--priam-ink-700);">
        You're running the business. Then a laptop walks out the door, a customer file ends up in
        the wrong inbox, or a supplier misses a deadline that was never tracked anywhere. Sound familiar?
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="priam-problem-card h-100">
          <div class="problem-head mb-3">
            <small class="priam-eyebrow d-block mb-2">Mon · 9:14 AM</small>
            "Has anyone seen Sarah's laptop?"
          </div>
          <p class="small mb-3" style="color: var(--priam-ink-700);">
            No record of who had what. No procedure for what to do next. No incident to point
            to in your audit.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-auto pt-3 border-top small fw-semibold" style="color: var(--bs-primary);">
            → Asset + Incident, linked
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="priam-problem-card h-100">
          <div class="problem-head mb-3">
            <small class="priam-eyebrow d-block mb-2">Tue · 3:42 PM</small>
            "I think I clicked something I shouldn't have."
          </div>
          <p class="small mb-3" style="color: var(--priam-ink-700);">
            Your phishing policy lives in a PDF nobody opened. There's no queue for the IT lead
            to pick this up.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-auto pt-3 border-top small fw-semibold" style="color: var(--bs-primary);">
            → Policy + Incident, connected
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="priam-problem-card h-100">
          <div class="problem-head mb-3">
            <small class="priam-eyebrow d-block mb-2">Fri · End of quarter</small>
            "Are we sure we're compliant?"
          </div>
          <p class="small mb-3" style="color: var(--priam-ink-700);">
            Last risk review was a spreadsheet someone built two years ago. You don't know what
            changed since.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-auto pt-3 border-top small fw-semibold" style="color: var(--bs-primary);">
            → Risk, continuously assessed
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
